Players and management staff of Rangers Int’l FC of Enugu on Saturday lost their cool after sharing points in their National Professional league Week 34 match with visitors Rivers Utd at the Awka Township stadium. Rangers Int’l scored a goal in the 55th-minute through Bala Akintude who fired a straight ball from outside the penalty box but this was rule as offside. Rangers also said they earned a penalty call which was ignored by the officials. The players and officials of the Enugu-based side, including Coach Abdu Maikiba who refused to speak to newsmen, protested openly alleging that they were robbed of victory. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that it took the intervention of bodyguards and security men to calm frayed nerves of the Enugu contingent who almost went physical with match officials. “This is wickedness, we got a goal they canceled it, we earned a penalty call, the referee ignored it, this is pure robbery”, one of the players shouted. On his part, Coach Stanley Egwuma of Rivers Utd said they played well against Rangers despite not scoring a goal. He said the result was good for the team and their quest to win the league, pointing out that it had not been easy for the team. He said he would not comment on the officiating as it was the prerogative of referees to determine what happens on the pitch. Rivers Utd are on top of the NPFL table with 71 points from 21 wins, eight draws and five losses after 34 games while Rangers are third on the table with 52 points from 34 matches after 14 wins, 10 wins and 10 wins. (NAN)